The paper discusses the design and implementation of a library for executing graph algorithms inside the Apache Accumulo database, which is a distributed key-value storage system. This makes it highly likely that the paper belongs to the cs.DB (database) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of graph algorithms, which are often used in distributed computing and data structures, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the emergence of the NewSQL paradigm, which is related to database management systems, suggesting that it could belong to the cs.CC (computational complexity and cryptography) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of matrix math systems, which is related to numerical analysis, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.NA (numerical analysis) sub-category.
